<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='358000' id='t-358000'>So I thought, &quot;Well, if you can't go to the government, go to the military.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='361000' id='t-361000'>So I went to the military</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='363000' id='t-363000'>and asked to borrow 300 radio stations.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='365000' id='t-365000'>They have more than the government,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='367000' id='t-367000'>and they've got more guns than the government.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='369000' id='t-369000'>So I asked them, could they help us</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='371000' id='t-371000'>in our fight against HIV.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='373000' id='t-373000'>And after I gave them statistics,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='375000' id='t-375000'>they said, &quot;Yes. Okay. You can use all the radio stations, television stations.&quot;</span>
